  "abstract": "ICGV 86155, ICGV 86156, ICGV 86158, ICGV 87378, and\r\nICGV 87921 Spanish peanut (ArachishypogaeaL. subsp.fastigiata\r\nWaldron var. vulgaris Harz) improved germplasm lines (Reg. no.\r\nGP-79 to GP-83, P1 594969 to P1 594973) were bred at the Asia\r\nCenter of the International Crops Research Institute for the Semi-\r\nArid Tropics (ICRISAT), Patancheru, Andhra Pradesh, India.\r\nThese five lines were released in 1995 by the Plant Materials\r\nIdentification Committee of ICRISAT for their fresh seed dormancy\r\nin the Spanish background.",
